{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17603299","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17603299"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:35:27+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:35:27+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15738"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15738","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15738"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.13,0.67,0.13,0.07,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8429"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71215"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8429","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8429"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15738"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56689"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"22"},{"type":"tags","id":"23"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1540"},{"type":"tags","id":"1652"},{"type":"tags","id":"3916"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7021"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20288"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20292"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71215","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/71215"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 28-year-old woman presents with vaginal bleeding three months after evacuation of a complete hydatidiform mole. Blood tests show:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EHuman chorionic gonadotropin: 250,000 IU/L (0-5)\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHistological examination of endometrial tissue shows sheets of cytotrophoblast and syncytiotrophoblast cells with marked nuclear atypia and frequent mitoses. There is extensive haemorrhage and necrosis.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Dysgerminoma","Choriocarcinoma","Mucinous adenocarcinoma","Squamous cell carcinoma","Clear cell carcinoma"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis case describes the classic features of \u003Cstrong\u003Echoriocarcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E, a highly malignant trophoblastic tumour. The key diagnostic features are:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EHistory of complete hydatidiform mole\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EMarkedly elevated human chorionic gonadotropin\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EHistological findings of malignant trophoblastic cells with haemorrhage\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options can be excluded:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDysgerminoma\u003C/strong\u003E is an ovarian germ cell tumour that typically occurs in young women but does not produce significant human chorionic gonadotropin\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMucinous adenocarcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E shows glandular differentiation with mucin production\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESquamous cell carcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E demonstrates keratinisation and intercellular bridges\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EClear cell carcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E has clear or hobnail cells arranged in tubular, papillary or solid patterns\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EChoriocarcinoma has a high propensity for early haematogenous spread but is very responsive to chemotherapy.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Choriocarcinoma is a highly malignant trophoblastic tumour that produces human chorionic gonadotropin","Choriocarcinoma most commonly follows a complete hydatidiform mole pregnancy","Key diagnostic features include markedly elevated hCG, malignant trophoblasts, and haemorrhage"],"references":["\u0022Choriocarcinoma -2- very high mag\u0022 by Nephron is licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 Unported license. https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Choriocarcinoma_-2-_very_high_mag.jpg","Makker V, MacKay H, Ray-Coquard I, Levine DA, Westin SN, Aoki D, Oaknin A. Endometrial cancer. Nat Rev Dis Primers. 2021 Dec 9;7(1):88. doi: 10.1038/s41572-021-00324-8. PMID: 34887451; PMCID: PMC9421940.","Felix AS, Brinton LA. Cancer Progress and Priorities: Uterine Cancer. Cancer Epidemiol Biomarkers Prev. 2018 Sep;27(9):985-994. doi: 10.1158/1055-9965.EPI-18-0264. PMID: 30181320; PMCID: PMC6504985.","Chelmow D, Brooks R, Cavens A, Huber-Keener K, Scott DM, Sheth SS, Whetstone S, Worly B, Burke W. Executive Summary of the Uterine Cancer Evidence Review Conference. Obstet Gynecol. 2022 Apr 1;139(4):626-643. doi: 10.1097/AOG.0000000000004711. Epub 2022 Mar 10. PMID: 35272316; PMCID: PMC8936160.","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56689"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15738"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21182"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21182","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21182"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/bcW6VphCP8hbrRBga9cV7GnpMl3XMj.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/bcW6VphCP8hbrRBga9cV7GnpMl3XMj.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":1500,"height